16/01/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Simitis met on Thursday (15 January) with the members of Bosnia and Herzegovina's tripartite presidency. In talks with Dragan Covic, Borislav Paravac and Sulejman Tihic, Simitis discussed bilateral co-operation in the area of economic aid, as well as Greece's participation in SFOR and the training of Bosnian police forces by the Greek police force ELAS. Simitis assured his guests of Greece's full support for their efforts to sign a Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU. (ANA, MPA, RTRS, PBS BiH - 15/01/04)
